ry_text\",\"text\":\"**Verifying Docker configurations**\\n\\nI'm looking at the Apache Kafka example, which says that if environment variables are set, all required properties need to be included. But it seems there are default configurations available if no environment variables are specified. I found a command from Docker Hub, like \\\"docker run -p 9092:9092 apache/kafka:4.0.0,\\\" and it looks like it might work. Actually, the quickstart suggests using \\\"docker run -p 9092:9092 apache/kafka:4.1.0.\\\" So, it seems I might need to use specific image tags too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"camel-kafka is a Camel component for communicating with an Apache Kafka broker; the resolved artifact already brings Camel core and kafka-clients transitively, but meaningful producer/consumer route coverage needs a real Kafka broker.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"docker_image\",\n      \"image\": \"apache/kafka:4.2.0\",\n      \"slug\": \"apache-kafka\",\n      \"reason\": \"The component documentation describes camel-kafka as communicating with an Apache Kafka message broker, and the artifact depends on kafka-clients 4.2.0; route-level coverage should publish to and consume from a broker rather than only instantiate configuration classes.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No extra Maven dependency was identified: camel-kafka:4.20.0 transitively includes camel-core-engine via camel-health and kafka-clients:4.2.0. Generated tests should start a single-node plaintext Kafka broker, wait until it accepts connections, use unique topic names, and configure Camel Kafka endpoints with the broker address via the `brokers` endpoint/component option. Keep tests focused on simple producer/consumer flows and cleanly stop the CamelContext and broker process.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Kafka startup is asynchronous; tests that do not wait for broker readiness may be flaky.\",\n    \"Using a fixed host port such as 9092 can collide with a local broker if one is already running.\",\n    \"Native Image verification remains authoritative; Kafka client networking and background threads may expose additional metadata needs only during native execution.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_089bf5f21f34aaeb016a28f81118588197bfbbd6da3a4f833f\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2049, "output": 861, "cacheRead": 34816, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37726, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781069824843, "responseId": "resp_089bf5f21f34aaeb016a28f80157f08197b7b08989b565b190"}}
